
[1]legitimate

   LEGIT'IMATE, a. [L. legitimus, from lex, law.]

   1. Lawfully begotten or born; born in wedlock; as legitimate heirs or
   children.

   2. Genuine; real; proceeding from a pure source; not false or spurious;
   as legitimate arguments or inferences.

                              LEGIT'IMATE, v.t.

   1. To make lawful

   2. To render legitimate; to communicate the rights of a legitimate
   child to one that is illegitimate; to invest with the rights of a
   lawful heir.
